The paper proposes a novel graph autoencoder framework for network embedding, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper focuses on graph convolutional autoencoder and its improvement, which is a subfield of deep learning and neural networks. The paper also discusses the reconstruction of node features and the adaptive-sharing adjacency method, which are related to computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
